                  <li>Overview</li>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Each Student will look at their story, the place they’re calling, think about the needs and culture of this space and think about, and find a map online that relays the same type of knowledge you're interested in sharing </li>
                  <ul>
                    <li>How does this map relay a story to its audience?</li>
                    <li>What did the cartographer do well? What did the cartographer do not so well?</li>
                    <li>How does this map change reality?</li>
                  </ul>
                    <li> Review the weekly materials to better understand mapping, placemaking, identity, and storytelling </li>
                    <li> Do not feel bound by reality! There are maps that tell fictional stories.</li>
